description:
&lt;p&gt;Applications are invited for the above opportunity. Working alongside the nursing leadership team in emergency care, we are embarking on a journey to transform nursing care in order to provide the best possible patient experience. Further to this we aim to increase staff morale and involvement, developing our emergency nursing education and training strategy and delivery to be outstanding. This will involve working with the multi-disciplinary team to develop an evidence based competency package for emergency nursing.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We would love to hear from highly motivated emergency nurses with who can fulfil the following criteria:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Degree level of education (or working towards) / or relevant demonstrable experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Current experience of clinical leadership in emergency care&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Current NMC registrant.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Post-registration qualification in emergency care – for example - ATNC/ATCC /ALS&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Post registration education qualification (or working towards) and mentorship qualification.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The leadership element of this role is essential and candidates must be able to demonstrate their skills to:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- Be a role model / effective leader&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- Exercise leadership skills to act as a catalyst for change.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- Develop and co-ordinate effective team working&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- Communicate on a regular basis with team regarding trust objectives, plans &amp; business developments&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is an ideal opportunity for a motivated, experienced and dynamic nurse to drive the improvement and success of the emergency department.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This is a full time post working 37.5 hours per week.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Alice Dudley - Senior Sister for Emergency Department on Tel: 01872253110 or email: alice.dudley@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
